cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.CC 

This paper discusses the combination of two important features in logic systems: consumption of resources and reasoning with exceptions. These features are relevant to several areas of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), cryptography (cs.CR), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
